<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870805-0105 </DOCNO><HL>  </HL><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> IBM MVIC SFETENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> KING OF PRUSSIA, Pa.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Safeguard Scientifics Inc. said Machine Vision International Corp. completed the previously announced purchase of the assets of Cherry Hill, N.J.-based TriStar Data Systems andamp; Office Automation Inc., as well as certain authorized retail outlets from International Business Machines Corp. The transactions cost a total of about $15 million.    Safeguard, which holds about a 48% stake in Machine Vision, is a diversified technology concern. It also is a creditor of Ann Arbor, Mich.-based Machine Vision, a provider of vision software for robotics systems. </TEXT></DOC>